text: Pope Symmachus was pope from 498 to 514 and succeeded by Pope Hormisdas. Symmachus is Born in Sardinia, Vandal Kingdom. His birth date is unknown. He died in 514 and he is Saint of the Catholic Church. His Feast day is on July 19. == Other websites == *Catholic Encyclopedia, Pope St. Symmachus (498â€“514) (1913).
